          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>Respected Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I find it impossible to obtain<lb/> a prayer Book
                                        for "the Day of Atonement"<lb/> separately from the whole
                                        Sett, which<lb/> I do not require having access always<lb/>
                                        to <persName>Mr Levy's</persName>–you were kind enough<lb/>
                                        the other evening to hint something, of<lb/> lending me one.
                                        if we gave power<lb/> it would confer a great favor. <lb/>
                                        save me an unecessary [?]<lb/> please answer me by Bearer
                                        and<lb/> oblige very Respectfully yours–</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <persName role="author">Joseph Benjamin</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
                              <p>
                                        <date>17 Sept. 1847</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>P.S. I think it due to inform you that I have or rather<lb/> shall
                                        take a seat for myself being fully time.</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <persName>Hon. Walter Lowrie</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Reverend Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p>Present</p>
                    </body>
